      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A humming AC unit without spinning fan can be quite unsettling, especially when it's vibrating. It's likely due to a refrigerant leak or a faulty compressor, which can be a bit of a \"goblin in the machine\" situation. You might need to call a professional to diagnose and fix the issue, as it could be a safety hazard if not handled properly. \n\nHowever, if you're feeling brave and want to take a peek, make sure to turn off the power to the unit at the circuit breaker or fuse box before you start. It's essential to be cautious, as an electrical shock could be a real \"goblin's surprise\" waiting to happen. \n\nAs you inspect the unit, keep an eye out for any signs of refrigerant leaks, which might appear as a hissing sound or a faint smell of ammonia. If you notice any of these, it's best to call a pro immediately. \n\nIf you're still unsure, consider consulting the user manual or contacting the manufacturer's customer support for guidance. They might be able to provide you with a \"goblin's guide\" to troubleshooting the issue.",
