      "content": "The phrase \"goblin in the machine\" is just a metaphorical expression, but I suppose it's a bit of a \"goblin's curse\" when it comes to complex electrical systems. In this case, it's likely a faulty capacitor or a malfunctioning relay that's causing the humming noise. \n\nA capacitor, in particular, might be the culprit, as it can develop internal resistance or wear out over time, leading to a humming or buzzing sound. It's a bit like a goblin hiding in the shadows, waiting to cause trouble when you least expect it. \n\nTo diagnose the issue, you can try checking the capacitor's value and condition. If it's old or damaged, it might be the source of the problem. You can also inspect the wiring and connections for any signs of wear or damage. If you're still unsure, it's always best to consult a professional, as they can help you navigate the \"goblin-infested\" world of electrical systems.",
